{
  "stem": "4361.5",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It was full of chunks of potatoes, chunks of meat, and here, this thing is dripping down my face, and I so want to lick it.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But I didn't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I didn't.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And then he sort of said, [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], called me a name.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Came the other girl, and she said, nein.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Nobody took it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "After I think the 10th or 15th girl, he kicked the barrel of soup, and it seeped.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Nobody touched it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "That's the one moment in my entire Auschwitz incarceration and elsewhere that I really-- I didn't think it through, but something made me say no, because it was Yom Kippur, and he was trying to defile me even more with-- with food, which was life, in a sense.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And I said no, and we didn't.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I really don't know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I really don't know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was-- I don't know whether I would have done it if the night before there wouldn't have been some sort of a Nidrei.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean that really evoked--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--some very strong feelings of-- of-- of memories of belonging somewhere, of being part of something, of having a legacy, a heritage.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, as I said, word must have gotten around that it was the [INAUDIBLE] Yom Kippur.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we did have that piece of bread, which was given at sundown, which was anyway OK.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was sundown.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then just one of the girls, somebody who-- who had probably a good voice, but more importantly, knew the melody and knew the words.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And just it was so quiet that when she sung, normally there were yells and screams and pushing and cryings and bickering among the inmates.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were miserable.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were terrible.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We were hungry.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We were frightened.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We were so lonely, so alone, so abandoned.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
